<main id="content" class="content"> <header> <h1 class="title">The Nineteenth Sunday After Pentecost</h1>
 <p class="subtitle" role="doc-subtitle">Jan 13, 2015 00:00</p>
</header> <p>
Here I am, Lord, <br></br>
asking for just <br></br>
one more chance.
</p>

 <p>
Why do you continue to use me?
What good am I to you?
</p>

 <p>
I am a <br></br>
flawed, <br></br>
broken, <br></br>
undependable <br></br>
tool.
</p>

 <p>
One that makes mistakes, <br></br>
and asks for second chances.
</p>

 <p>
But I hear a gentle voice <br></br>
whispering a message of hope, <br></br>
that my heart longs to hear…
</p>

 <p>
That even a flawed and broken tool <br></br>
can make something beautiful <br></br>
when it’s used by the master.
</p>

 <p>
 <i>Amen</i>
</p>


